<article id="node-132816" class="view-mode--teaser-tile effect--view-mode  cf view-mode--hover-effect"  about="/war/articles/marine-killed-peleliu-accounted-80-years-after-battle">

      <div class="col-image">
              <a href="/war/articles/marine-killed-peleliu-accounted-80-years-after-battle" target="_self">
    
<img loading="lazy" src="/themes/nwwiim/images/loaders/placeholder.gif" width="491" height="328" alt="A Marine Corps amphibious tractor (LVT) on “Orange” beach at Peleliu" typeof="foaf:Image" class="b-lazy" data-src="/sites/default/files/styles/max_650x650/public/2024-09/lvt-peleliu.png" />
<noscript><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/max_650x650/public/2024-09/lvt-peleliu.png" alt="A Marine Corps amphibious tractor (LVT) on “Orange” beach at Peleliu"/></noscript>




</a>
          </div>
  
  <div class="col-content">

    <div class="f--label f--uppercase effect--f">
  <div class="field field--name-field-article-type field--type-entity-reference field--label-above">
    <div class="field__label">Article Type</div>
              <div class="field__item"><a href="/war/articles" hreflang="en">Article</a></div>
          </div>
</div>

    
    
                    <h3 class="f--title f--tertiary"><a href="/war/articles/marine-killed-peleliu-accounted-80-years-after-battle" rel="bookmark" target="_self">Marine Killed at Peleliu Accounted For 80 Years After Battle</a></h3>
            
    

    
          <div class="f--desc">
        <p>After 80 years, the remains of Private First Class John Henry Newstrom, a US Marine killed during the Battle of Peleliu in 1944, have been identified and will be returned home thanks to a joint recovery effort by the US and Japanese governments.</p>
      </div>
        
    
  </div>

</article>
</div>

      
      
    </main>
  
  
  

  
  
